00:34:13.369 --> 00:34:16.268
This is your mental image.

00:34:16.268 --> 00:34:20.728
This is what's called
exponential growth.

00:34:20.728 --> 00:34:24.073
It's obvious how that happens.

00:34:24.073 --> 00:34:30.874
And we're going to model this
population, we're going to first

00:34:30.874 --> 00:34:35.000
assume unlimited resources.

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:49.352
OK, so we're going to say that
the rate of population increase

00:34:49.352 --> 00:35:02.764
is equal to the average birth
rate minus the average death

00:35:02.764 --> 00:35:11.000
rate times the number of cells.

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:17.079
OK, so we are going to now turn
this into math,

00:35:17.079 --> 00:35:24.348
and that is to say the dN/dt,
the increase in population

00:35:24.348 --> 00:35:32.806
where N is the population number
is equal to the birth rate minus

00:35:32.806 --> 00:35:39.546
the death rate times N which is
the number of cells,

00:35:39.546 --> 00:35:41.000
OK?

00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:51.557
And then, we're going to let B
minus D, the birth rate minus

00:35:51.557 --> 00:35:58.000
the death rate,
be what we call r.

00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:11.013
And, this is what's called the
intrinsic rate of increase of a

00:36:11.013 --> 00:36:13.360
population.

00:36:13.360 --> 00:36:19.333
OK, what are the units of r?

00:36:19.333 --> 00:36:30.000
One over time,
exactly, time to the minus one.

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:34.294
So, let's look at that more
carefully.

00:36:34.294 --> 00:36:40.562
And also, it's a little
misleading to say it's the rate

00:36:40.562 --> 00:36:46.250
of increase because r can be
positive or negative,

00:36:46.250 --> 00:36:48.687
however it turns out.

00:36:48.687 --> 00:36:55.535
It can be positive or negative,
but that's what it's called.

00:36:55.535 --> 00:36:59.133
